cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is about improving the performance of neural networks through the introduction of a new activation function called "Power Linear Unit" (PoLU). The paper focuses on image classification tasks and uses benchmark datasets such as MNIST, CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100, Street View House Numbers (SVHN), and ImageNet. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the nonlinearity capacity of neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the results, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
